==English==

===Etymology===
A common misquotation of a line from [[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]]'s 1595 play ''[[w:King John|King John]]'':
:"''To '''gild''' refined gold, to paint '''the lily''', to throw a perfume on the violet, to smooth the ice, or add another hue unto the rainbow, or with taper-light to seek the beauteous eye of heaven to garnish, is wasteful and ridiculous excess.''"

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-gild the lily.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Intransitive verb===
'''to [[gild]] the [[lily]]'''
# to [[embellish]] something that does not need it
# to add unnecessary [[bells and whistles]]